Restriction of golden parachutes
The chairman of the Senate banking committee, Christopher Dodd, the chief negotiator, said lawmakers had agreed on a responsibility for the money program, protecting taxpayers from losses, concluding benefits, and a timetable for financing the plan.
The new law will also restrict the so-called golden parachutes for directors of the companies involved in the programme and establish a committee to oversee the fund.
The Treasury is to lead it.
“We’ve been working very hard on it and making great progress toward an agreement that works and is important to the market and to all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also expects help for homeowners who have problems repaying their mortgage.
The government should negotiate new installments on mortgages it buys up, with the goal being to lower the monthly cost to debtors and allow them to keep their homes.
Marek: Psychological Aid
The proposed plan is a good idea, according to Patria Finance chief economist David Marek, but it will be very difficult to implement.
"That's because you don't know by what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets are bought up.
This will be crucial to how the financial sector and the government divide the losses among themselves," Marek told iHNed.cz this week.
Whether the plan will be adopted now or early next week is not decisive in Marek’s view.
“It’s more important that Congress members agree to support the plan and pass it as soon as possible.
The psychological significance of the agreement that there is a passing is the most important at this moment,” Marek stressed.
Duel on knife cutting edge: MP3 player against mobile phones.
We will advise you on your choice
While almost any phone can play MP3 files, no MP3 player can make phone calls yet.
Therefore, of course, it looks like it is better to buy only one phone.
Yet, there are plenty of reasons why you should get a standalone player.
The choice depends entirely on the type of use and the claims of the future owner.
Surely you can hardly buy a great expensive record player at home to listen to Maxim Turbulenc's latest album.
Once such musical novelties do not appear on LPs, and from a qualitative point of view there is no objective reason for this either.
However, if you have LPs with art rock, jazz or blues on the shelf, you probably dream of at least one.
This is also the case with traveling music, i.e. with compressed music, in a simplified way - music in MP3 format.
There are also price and quality categories.
For one it may not be acceptable to spend eight thousand crowns for a player, but likewise a pink floyd fan will hardly handle headphones for twenty crowns from the market.
Two extremes between which there is enough space for everyone.
The selection is wide-ranging.
The battery life is also crucial.
Some good music players can play much more than just music, but what mobile phones can do, they don’t even make it implying.
No modern device can be used as universally as the phone.
In addition to the primary features, the phone and the Sims, it can play music and videos, both record, it has a better, sometimes a worse camera, and maybe it can also navigate.
And if you also include the smartphones and communicators, you almost have a small computer in your pocket.
