In this respect, music players (especially the simplest ones) are significantly more powerful.
That’s why you should count on cheap phones that they can’t play music for more than a few hours.
If you are still talking on the phone from time to time, you prefer to buy a charger for the office - this also applies to more expensive devices.
With MP3 players, you won’t have this problem, even the less good ones last at least 9 hours of uninterrupted operation with one-time recharging.
There is another problem when you want to play the music on your phone.
Unfortunately, only a small part of the devices have a USB port, and not every phone can be connected directly to a PC without special software.
Of course, you can overplay the music directly to a storage medium, but only a few card readers can handle the tiny memory cards that are used in mobile phones without reduction.
For players, except for exceptions (iPod), you do not need special software.
You only need to feed the device with music from your PC via USB port.
Most mobile phones and players create a music library themselves, ordered by the name of the performer, the title of the album, the genre or for example the rating by users.
