Talking in sleep
Some children speak at night
I don’t mean those who wake up and tell us what happened the day before, but the children who talk in their sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it does not matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Surely, more than one of you has been told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, as during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason that causes this appearance.
Often, connections with other phenomena in sleep are sought, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overload.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks quietly in individual words, whispers, or it may be quite the opposite (crying, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the statement is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and consult with a specialist to check for a problem that causes anxiety and occurs in this way.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Do not try to excite the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful television programs that are terrible and a little too wild.
For nervous children who are recommended to relax, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner calm.
This helps the child sleep calmly.
When speaking occurs in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless to the child and the next day he will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will tear him out of sleep.
Although the child speaks, he sleeps, so he rests.
Remember, if he is scared after a couple of apparitions, it is recommended to seek advice or find out what reason the child has for the fear.
When they understand what it says (which isn’t that usual), the child doesn’t put pressure on them to conduct an interrogation and get more information out.
This way you will not be able to achieve anything because when the child is asleep, he is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Besides, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it dreams of and why it says it, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Maybe, it doesn't tell the child that you hear it at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
This causes a lot of fear.
So, don’t worry, it’s nothing bad, it’s a moment that only takes a few minutes.
