Listening to loud music over a longer period of time using portable music devices, such as Mp3 players, can lead to permanent hearing damage.
This is reported by the European Commission, which cites the opinion of the EU’s Csrseri (Scientific Committee on Current and Recently Identified Health Risks) in a report released today in Brussels.
“It is clear from the report that 5-10% of those who listen to loud music on portable music devices for at least five years a week for more than an hour a day risk permanent hearing loss.”
"I'm worried that such a large number of teenagers, who usually put wearable music devices and mobile phones on high volumes, will irretrievably damage their hearing without knowing it," Kuneva said.
"From the scientific findings - it is said by the European Union - there is a clear risk that urges rapid action.
